{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":598,"text":"It was the middle of summer\nand well past closing time"},{"time":3211,"text":"in the downtown Berkeley bar\nwhere my friend Polly and I"},{"time":5898,"text":"worked together as bartenders."},{"time":8693,"text":"Usually at the end of our shift\nwe had a drink -- but not that night."},{"time":13732,"text":"\"I'm pregnant."},{"time":15224,"text":"Not sure what I'm going\nto do yet,\" I told Polly."},{"time":18729,"text":"Without hesitation, she replied,\n\"I've had an abortion.\""},{"time":22819,"text":"Before Polly, no one had ever told me\nthat she'd had an abortion."},{"time":28631,"text":"I'd graduated from college\njust a few months earlier"},{"time":31336,"text":"and I was in a new relationship\nwhen I found out that I was pregnant."},{"time":35797,"text":"When I thought about my choices,\nI honestly did not know how to decide,"},{"time":40534,"text":"what criteria I should use."},{"time":43459,"text":"How would I know what\nthe right decision was?"},{"time":46408,"text":"I worried that I would regret \nan abortion later."},{"time":51044,"text":"Coming of age on the beaches\nof Southern California,"},{"time":53785,"text":"I grew up in the middle of \nour nation's abortion wars."},{"time":57646,"text":"I was born in a trailer on the third\nanniversary of Roe vs. Wade."},{"time":63578,"text":"Our community was surfing Christians."},{"time":66265,"text":"We cared about God, the less fortunate,\nand the ocean."},{"time":70022,"text":"Everyone was pro-life."},{"time":72413,"text":"As a kid, the idea of abortion made me so\nsad that I knew if I ever got pregnant"},{"time":78125,"text":"I could never have one."},{"time":81412,"text":"And then I did."},{"time":84789,"text":"It was a step towards the unknown."},{"time":87531,"text":"But Polly had given me\na very special gift:"},{"time":90305,"text":"the knowledge that I wasn't alone"},{"time":92687,"text":"and the realization that abortion\nwas something that we can talk about."},{"time":97055,"text":"Abortion is common."},{"time":99370,"text":"According to the Guttmacher Institute,\none in three women in America"},{"time":102714,"text":"will have an abortion in their lifetime."},{"time":108147,"text":"But for the last few decades, the dialogue\naround abortion in the United States"},{"time":112050,"text":"has left little room for anything beyond \npro-life and pro-choice."},{"time":115944,"text":"It's political and polarizing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118688,"text":"But as much as abortion is hotly debated,\nit's still rare for us,"},{"time":122982,"text":"whether as fellow women\nor even just as fellow people,"},{"time":126898,"text":"to talk with one another\nabout the abortions that we have."},{"time":132028,"text":"There is a gap."},{"time":133430,"text":"Between what happens in politics\nand what happens in real life,"},{"time":137215,"text":"and in that gap, a battlefield mentality."},{"time":139794,"text":"An \"are you with us \nor against us?\" stance takes root."},{"time":144058,"text":"This isn't just about abortion."},{"time":146655,"text":"There are so many important issues \nthat we can't talk about."},{"time":152278,"text":"And so finding ways to shift the conflict\nto a place of conversation"},{"time":157524,"text":"is the work of my life."},{"time":161410,"text":"There are two main ways to get started."},{"time":164332,"text":"One way is to listen closely.\n"},{"time":166634,"text":"And the other way is to share stories."},{"time":171073,"text":"So, 15 years ago, I cofounded\nan organization called Exhale"},{"time":174664,"text":"to start listening to people \nwho have had abortions."},{"time":178593,"text":"The first thing we did was create \na talk-line, where women and men"},{"time":181963,"text":"could call to get emotional support."},{"time":184862,"text":"Free of judgment and politics,\nbelieve it or not, nothing like our sevice"},{"time":189064,"text":"had ever existed."},{"time":192257,"text":"We needed a new framework that could \nhold all the experiences that we were"},{"time":196467,"text":"hearing on our talk-line."},{"time":198934,"text":"The feminist who regrets her abortion."},{"time":201555,"text":"The Catholic who is grateful for hers."},{"time":204132,"text":"The personal experiences that weren't \nfitting neatly into one box or the other."},{"time":209416,"text":"We didn't think it was right \nto ask women to pick a side."},{"time":213467,"text":"We wanted to show them that\nthe whole world was on their side,"},{"time":218469,"text":"as they were going through this deeply\npersonal experience."},{"time":222964,"text":"So we invented \"pro-voice.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":226191,"text":"Beyond abortion, pro-voice works on hard\nissues that we've struggled with globally"},{"time":230751,"text":"for years,"},{"time":232022,"text":"issues like immigration, religious\ntolerance, violence against women."},{"time":237315,"text":"It also works on deeply personal topics \nthat might only matter to you"},{"time":241366,"text":"and your immediate family and friends."},{"time":243989,"text":"They have a terminal illness, \ntheir mother just died,"},{"time":247878,"text":"they have a child with special needs\nand they can't talk about it."},{"time":253636,"text":"Listening and storytelling are\nthe hallmarks of pro-voice practice."},{"time":259302,"text":"Listening and storytelling."},{"time":261484,"text":"That sounds pretty nice."},{"time":263551,"text":"Sounds maybe, easy?\nWe could all do that."},{"time":267150,"text":"It's not easy.\nIt's very hard."},{"time":270354,"text":"Pro-voice is hard because we are talking\nabout things everyone's fighting about"},{"time":276233,"text":"or the things that no one \nwants to talk about."},{"time":279409,"text":"I wish I could tell you that when you \ndecide to be pro-voice, that you'll find"},{"time":286365,"text":"beautiful moments of breakthrough \nand gardens full of flowers,"},{"time":290615,"text":"where listening and storytelling\ncreates wonderful \"a-ha\" moments."},{"time":295220,"text":"I wish I could tell you that there would\nbe a feminist welcoming party for you,"},{"time":299279,"text":"or that there's a long-lost sisterhood\nof people who are just ready"},{"time":302641,"text":"to have your back when you get slammed."},{"time":306301,"text":"But it can be vulnerable and exhausting \nto tell our own stories"},{"time":310546,"text":"when it feels like nobody cares."},{"time":314520,"text":"And if we truly listen to one another,"},{"time":318755,"text":"we will hear things that demand\nthat we shift our own perceptions."},{"time":325921,"text":"There is no perfect time\nand there is no perfect place"},{"time":328827,"text":"to start a difficult conversation."},{"time":331811,"text":"There's never a time when everyone will be\non the same page, share the same lens,"},{"time":337414,"text":"or know the same history."},{"time":341153,"text":"So, let's talk about listening\nand how to be a good listener."},{"time":346650,"text":"There's lots of ways to be a good listener\nand I'm going to give you just a couple."},{"time":350905,"text":"One is to ask open-ended questions."},{"time":353807,"text":"You can ask yourself or someone \nthat you know,"},{"time":356519,"text":"\"How are you feeling?\""},{"time":359519,"text":"\"What was that like?\""},{"time":362166,"text":"\"What do you hope for, now?\""},{"time":366368,"text":"Another way to be a good listener \nis to use reflective language."},{"time":370757,"text":"If someone is talking about\ntheir own personal experience,"},{"time":373661,"text":"use the words that they use."},{"time":376169,"text":"If someone is talking about an abortion\nand they say the word \"baby,\""},{"time":379539,"text":"you can say \"baby.\""},{"time":381483,"text":"If they say \"fetus,\"\nyou can say \"fetus.\""},{"time":384479,"text":"If someone describes themselves\nas gender queer to you,"},{"time":387224,"text":"you can say \"gender queer.\""},{"time":389782,"text":"If someone kind of looks like a he,\nbut they say they're a she -- it's cool."},{"time":393620,"text":"Call that person a she."},{"time":396081,"text":"When we reflect the language of the person\nwho is sharing their own story,"},{"time":399647,"text":"we are conveying that we are interested\nin understanding who they are"},{"time":405029,"text":"and what they're going through."},{"time":407745,"text":"The same way that we hope people are \ninterested in knowing us."},{"time":413062,"text":"So, I'll never forget being in one \nof the Exhale counselor meetings,"},{"time":416473,"text":"listening to a volunteer talk about how\nshe was getting a lot of calls"},{"time":420374,"text":"from Christian women who \nwere talking about God."},{"time":424114,"text":"Now, some of our volunteers are religious,\nbut this particular one was not."},{"time":428247,"text":"At first, it felt a little weird for her \nto talk to callers about God."},{"time":432852,"text":"So, she decided to get comfortable."},{"time":435282,"text":"And she stood in front of her mirror \nat home, and she said the word \"God.\""},{"time":439671,"text":"\"God.\""},{"time":440785,"text":"\"God.\""},{"time":441505,"text":"\"God.\""},{"time":442225,"text":"\"God.\""},{"time":443325,"text":"\"God.\""},{"time":444282,"text":"\"God.\""},{"time":445801,"text":"Over and over and over again\nuntil the word no longer felt strange"},{"time":449081,"text":"coming out her mouth."},{"time":451455,"text":"Saying the word God did not turn this \nvolunteer into a Christian,"},{"time":455395,"text":"but it did make her a much \nbetter listener of Christian women."},{"time":462693,"text":"So, another way to be pro-voice\nis to share stories,"},{"time":466576,"text":"and one risk that you take on, when you\nshare your story with someone else,"},{"time":470796,"text":"is that given the same\nset of circumstances as you"},{"time":473983,"text":"they might actually\nmake a different decision."},{"time":477227,"text":"For example, if you're telling a story \nabout your abortion,"},{"time":481423,"text":"realize that she might have had the baby."},{"time":486284,"text":"She might have placed for adoption."},{"time":489790,"text":"She might have told her parents \nand her partner -- or not."},{"time":494503,"text":"She might have felt relief and confidence,\neven though you felt sad and lost."},{"time":500450,"text":"This is okay."},{"time":503723,"text":"Empathy gets created the moment we\nimagine ourselves in someone else's shoes."},{"time":509606,"text":"It doesn't mean we all have \nto end up in the same place."},{"time":514729,"text":"It's not agreement, it's not sameness\nthat pro-voice is after."},{"time":521207,"text":"It creates a culture and a society that \nvalues what make us special and unique."},{"time":527569,"text":"It values what makes us human,\nour flaws and our imperfections."},{"time":532932,"text":"And this way of thinking allows us to see\nour differences with respect,"},{"time":537551,"text":"instead of fear."},{"time":540386,"text":"And it generates the empathy that we need"},{"time":542600,"text":"to overcome all the ways\nthat we try to hurt one another."},{"time":546026,"text":"Stigma, shame, prejudice, \ndiscrimination, oppression."},{"time":552690,"text":"Pro-voice is contagious,\nand the more it's practiced"},{"time":557603,"text":"the more it spreads."},{"time":563149,"text":"So, last year I was pregnant again."},{"time":566253,"text":"This time I was looking forward \nto the birth of my son."},{"time":570350,"text":"And while pregnant, I had never been asked\nhow I was feeling so much in all my life."},{"time":576927,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":578346,"text":"And however I replied, whether I was\nfeeling wonderful and excited"},{"time":582408,"text":"or scared and totally freaked out,"},{"time":585217,"text":"there was always someone there\ngiving me a \"been there\" response."},{"time":589578,"text":"It was awesome."},{"time":591350,"text":"It was a welcome, yet dramatic\ndeparture from what I experience"},{"time":596520,"text":"when I talk about\nmy mixed feelings of my abortion."},{"time":601087,"text":"Pro-voice is about the real stories\nof real people"},{"time":604864,"text":"making an impact on the way abortion"},{"time":607444,"text":"and so many other politicized\nand stigmatized issues"},{"time":611542,"text":"are understood and discussed."},{"time":613857,"text":"From sexuality and mental health\nto poverty and incarceration."},{"time":619562,"text":"Far beyond definition\nas single right or wrong decisions,"},{"time":623050,"text":"our experiences can exist on a spectrum."},{"time":628478,"text":"Pro-voice focuses that conversation\non human experience"},{"time":632800,"text":"and it makes support and respect\npossible for all."},{"time":638755,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":640390,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}